gate: OPEN
status: IN_FLIGHT
owner: Oleg (pedchenkooleh-coo)
issue: https://github.com/CT-CROP/CROP-front/issues/1540
as_of: 2026-06-03
note: |
  Oleg working on it. No PR yet.
  Target: MobileChapterDrawer shows image thumbnails (not text-only) on mobile.
  Do not create new drawer — reuse MobileChapterDrawer (chapter-sidebar.tsx, 258 lines).
  Test: pinch-zoom must still work after change.
sprint: S06
track: B
task: B2
title: "feat(mobile): expose diagram image-scroll panel on mobile assembly view"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: high
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("on mobile you only have that menu on the left side... a lot of
    menus that are meaningless to you")
  - meetup-02-06-26 ("this doesn't exist for mobile" — referring to the hover/scroll
    image strip on the parts diagram screen)
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND]

impact: |
  On desktop, the assembly page (`/parts-diagrams/[brand]/assemblies/[assemblyCode]`)
  shows a scrollable image strip so users can visually browse diagram sections
  ("I know it when I see it"). On mobile, users only see the text-only chapter list.
  Most customers browse on mobile. Without image-based browsing on mobile, the
  strongest feature of the platform is invisible to the majority of users.

description: |
  The desktop assembly view has an image-scroll overlay (visible via hover / the
  popout John created). The `MobileChapterDrawer` (features/assemblies/chapter-sidebar.tsx)
  exists and handles drawer open/close but currently shows only the text chapter list.

  Goal: on mobile, when the assembly page loads, the chapter-part-search panel
  (currently desktop-only) should be accessible. The user should be able to:
  1. See thumbnail previews of diagram sections (same images the desktop hover shows).
  2. Tap a thumbnail → jump to that section in the schematic viewer.
  3. Use the search-within-diagram filter (the text filter input in the popout panel).

  Implementation path:
  - `assembly-interactive-view.tsx` controls the chapter/image panel visibility.
    Inspect whether the image-strip panel is hidden via a CSS breakpoint or via
    JS state. If CSS: expose it on mobile with a toggle button. If JS: wire the
    toggle into `MobileChapterDrawer` trigger.
  - `chapter-sidebar.tsx` / `MobileChapterDrawer`: the drawer already exists;
    if the image strip content is in `chapter-assembly-list.tsx` or `chapter-row.tsx`,
    route that content into the mobile drawer.
  - The `use-zoom-pan.ts` hook drives the schematic viewport on touch — ensure
    the drawer open/close doesn't interfere with zoom-pan gestures.

scope:
  in:
    - Expose the chapter-image-strip content inside MobileChapterDrawer
    - "Browse diagrams" button / FAB visible on mobile assembly page
    - Tap thumbnail → schematic viewer scrolls/snaps to that section
    - Image filter input works on mobile keyboard (no overflow issues)
    - Vitest: MobileChapterDrawer renders chapter images when provided
  out:
    - Redesigning the desktop layout
    - Changing the zoom-pan gesture model
    - Implementing pinch-zoom (already handled by use-zoom-pan.ts — don't break it)

invariants:
  - No React.memo / unjustified useMemo/useCallback
  - All touch targets ≥ 44x44px (WCAG 2.5.5)
  - Drawer close must not break the back-navigation (history.back() should still work)
  - Use MobileChapterDrawer — do not create a new drawer component

acceptance:
  - Mobile (375px viewport): assembly page has a visible "Browse Diagrams" trigger
  - Tap trigger → drawer opens with image thumbnails of diagram sections
  - Tap thumbnail → schematic viewer shows that section (same behavior as desktop click)
  - Text filter inside drawer filters the thumbnail list
  - Drawer dismisses on swipe-down or tap-outside; does not interfere with schematic pan

dep: none (isolated to assembly view — can parallel with B1)
output: features/assemblies/chapter-sidebar.tsx + assembly-interactive-view.tsx changes
